) and the (PARTY NAME): licenses for illegals "makes a lot of sense."</b> </p><p><b> <u>the (PARTY NAME) believe in legitimizing illegal immigrants by granting them driver's licenses:</u> </b> </p><p><b>at last night's (PARTY NAME) debate, sen. (candidate full) (d-ny) said giving driver's license to illegal immigrants "makes a lot of sense."</b> nbc's tim russert: "senator (candidate last), i just want to make sure what i heard. do you, the new york senator (candidate full), support the new york governor's plan to give illegal immigrants a driver's license?" ... sen. (candidate full): "you know, tim, this is where everybody plays gotcha. it makes a lot of sense. what is the governor supposed to do? he is dealing with a serious problem." (msnbc, (PARTY NAME) presidential candidate debate, philadelphia, pa, 10/30/07) </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- sen. (candidate last) has previously said giving licenses to illegals "makes a lot of sense."</b> "'i know exactly what governor spitzer's trying to do, and it makes a lot of sense because he's trying to get people out of the shadows. he's trying to say, "o.k., come forward and we will give you this license,"' sen. (candidate full), d-n.y., recently told the telegraph editorial board." (eduardo a. de oliveira, "police and customs working together," <em>nashua</em> [nh] <em>telegraph</em>, 10/22/07) </p></blockquote> <p><b>sen. (candidate full) (d-il) agrees that licenses for illegals are "the right idea."</b> sen. (candidate full): "i think that it is a -- the right idea. and i disagree with chris, because there is a public safety concern. we can make sure that drivers who are illegal come out of the shadows, that they can be tracked, that they are properly trained, and that will make our roads safer. that doesn't negate the need for us to reform illegal immigration." (msnbc, (PARTY NAME) presidential candidate debate, philadelphia, pa, 10/30/07)</p></span>



